            {"text":"DBSCAN does not require the user to set the number of clusters a priori, unlike k-means","source_id":"Page 201"},
            {"text":"DBSCAN can capture clusters of complex shapes, unlike agglomerative clustering","source_id":"Page 202"},
            {"text":"DBSCAN is somewhat slower than agglomerative clustering and k-means, but still scales to relatively large datasets","source_id":"Page 201"}
         ],
         "key_message":"DBSCAN has advantages and disadvantages compared to other clustering algorithms.",
